Ask HN: What jobs would allow you to program your own projects almost full time?
text:
I was wondering, there must be jobs that allow you to be paid for full time work, and spend most of your time coding.

The only job I could up with though is maybe car park attendant where you sit in the booth. If you found a quite carpark you might get to spend most of your time coding?

Any other jobs like this?

Fair share for a CTO in a Web3 company
text:
Hi HN,

I've been offered a CTO post on a wannabe web3 company.

There is already 3 founders, and they are (like everyone else) looking for their technical founder.

They all bring 150k to the table, I will not.

1 understand crypto/web3, the 2 others have relations (clients & investors), but don't know much of the space.

The project is not wow, but can clearly generate money easily.

They will probably pay me 50% market salary, I just don't know what would be a fair % share to ask for without looking greedy. I also don't want to end up with a low amount which would mean I can't influence decisions.

My main issue with this project is that I feel like it will rely a lot on me and web3 people who know how to code in solidity are rare.

The good thing is they all have strong relations, one of the current founders already made a good exit before.

People of HN, what % shares looks fair to you in that context?

Thanks to the community
